FBIS3-33812 "drnes021_j_94010" FBIS-NES-94-021 Document Type:Daily Report 1 Feb 1994 ARABIAN PENINSULA Yemen Minister on `Practical Measures' JN3101155994 Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network in Arabic 1514 GMT 31 Jan 94 JN3101155994 Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network Language: Arabic Article Type:BFN [Text] Yemeni Minister of Interior Brigadier General Yahya al-Mutawakkil has denied that the kidnapping of three French nationals northwest of Sanaa last week was politically motivated. In press statements today, he added that the kidnappers motive in taking the three hostages, one man and two women, is to provoke the government and make unrealistic demands. He went on to say that his ministry has taken practical measures to besiege the kidnappers in case they do not surrender and free the hostages.
